Reasoning: The paper discusses a new network sharing arrangement between large facilities and traditional operators in wireless cellular networks. It proposes a new evaluation framework for resource allocation that takes into account financial as well as physical resource constraints. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of spectrum and core network access, which suggests that it may also belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The paper also discusses the design of the wireless network architecture, which suggests that it may belong to the Signal and Image Processing (cs.SI) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of a socio-technical evaluation framework based on ruin-theory, which suggests that it may belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the lack of a business case for network sharing, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computer Engineering (cs.CE) sub-category.
